President Donald Trump met with President Xi Jinping of China at the G20 Summit in Germany. They discussed the threat posed by North Korea's nuclear and ballistic missile programs and the need to respond to North Korea's recent test of an intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM). Both leaders reiterated their commitment to a denuclearized Korean Peninsula. They also discussed other areas of the bilateral relationship, including economic issues such as reciprocal trade and market access. Trump and Xi instructed their security and economic teams to make progress in future dialogues.